In this op-ed, President Obama emphasizes the need for global economic cooperation and comprehensive action to address the ongoing global economic challenges. He highlights the interconnectedness of economies and the urgent need for coordinated efforts to jump-start recovery and prevent future crises. Obama urges the leaders of the G-20 to take swift action to stimulate growth, restore credit, and extend support to countries and people facing the greatest risk. He also emphasizes the importance of comprehensive reforms to regulatory and supervisory frameworks to prevent irresponsible risk-taking. Obama concludes by calling for a new kind of global economic cooperation that promotes sustained growth, innovation, entrepreneurship, and opportunity.